<br>
Undead of Norrath, with this momentous occasion, we will be able to take part in one of the most pleasurable activities in Norrath -- killing Paladins.  Now we all know how paladins have been, for the most part, the most laughable class in EverQuest next to wood elf warriors (also known as tone deaf bards), however being able to beat on a paladin like a pinata is probably the most desirable activity available in the game.<br>
<br>
My undead breatheren, no matter how nice of a gift this is, it is not without a disadvantage.  More and more paladins will be leaving the game soon, so be proactive about seeking out the paladins for their beatings.  If necessary, wait for them in the character select screeen to really give them a surprise!<br>
<br>
To celebrate this momentous occasion, we will be holding a &quot;million bone march&quot; through the streets of Freeport.  We intend to follow the parade with a charge into North Freeport, hog-tie the Paladin guild master, make him squeel, &quot;Arrreeeewwwwww!&quot; until our jawbones dislodge from too much laughter.<br>
<br>
We look forward to your prompt attendance.  This event begins tomorrow at 3pm by the docks.  Be sure hold onto your ticket stub for a chance to win a lifetime supply of paladin pickles, sponsored by Boomba the Big Enterprises(Ltd.) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub28.ezboard.com/uaekarainbringer.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aeka Rainbringer</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle><b>I shall bring you rain!!!</b></span><br>  Posts: 205<br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/20/02 2:59:38 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub28.ezboard.com/fdrinal28133frm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1518.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://sageofrain.com/archer.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: /Flame Slay Undead Nerf</span><hr size=1> The nerf isn't happening anymore. Probably because &quot;The issue is that there are no amount of AAs the warrior can buy to also raise his situational damage by such a large amount&quot; isn't really a sensible reason. Paladins and Clerics are *supposed* to have high situational prowess versus undead.<br>
